    "ML has been widely employed to screen ionic conductors for solid-state batteries 73.",
    "Recently, Yang et al.",
    "74 proposed a dynamic database for solidstate inorganic electrolytes, providing a promising foundation for application of ML.",
    "ML research on inorganic electrolytes is highly versatile, encompassing the prediction of ionic conductivity, classification of crystal structures, characterization of solid-state electrolytes, and screening of applicable inorganic electrolytes.",
    "We emphasize that three main challenges in applying ML for the discovery of solid-state inorganic electrolytes include 1) Accurate prediction of the ionic conductivity and interfacial resistance for a wide range of ionic conductors; 2) Evaluation of the stability of solid-state ionic conductors; 3) Estimation of the mechanical strength and the largescale fabrication capabilities."
